Here in this age we live in it seems like nearly everyone and their
brother are posting their songs on the internet.  In some cases these
are songs they wrote themselves.  I have a feeling that few of these
people have actually bothered to copyright their songs.  Is there a
real danger of being ripped off when people post their songs on the
internet to get some exposure?  Or by posting their songs do they
inherently make some legal claim of ownership?

I'm sure most of the people who do this probably don't take music that
seriously to begin with, but I can't help but be curious about it.
Thus far I've resisted the temptation to post music of my own on the
internet for the reasons listed above, but maybe I'm just missing out
on a chance to share.  I always used to say that if someone would
bother to steal one of my songs I would probably take it as a
compliment.  Now, probably not.
