AFAIK:

You don't need to file for copyright. Any creative work, in the absence
of a contract or some other legal binding stuff that transfers
copyright, is automatically &quot;Copyright &lt;creation date&gt;, All rights reserved &lt;creator&gt;&quot;.

And the existence of a public forum post of it would make quite
straightforward to claim one wrote it first.

As I stated at the start, that's as far as I know, and I am no lawyer.
